Agreed, am working on getting some of the scrubber tests running against Swift at the moment.

Patch Set 1:

This bug should apply to any backend, so you might be able to get a comparable test using the filesystem store.
Uploaded patch set 2.

Patch Set 2:

>> This bug should apply to any backend...
Technically yes, though the nature of this bug is that the previous fix only appears to work when using a file backend; Swift (and I'm assuming other networked backends) still suffer from the delete threads not starting.

The new approach should be correct for all, patchset 2 duplicates test_scrubber_app to run against Swift so both filesystem and networked backends are being tested.
